## Superseded from mojo-glibc-env-awareness

```yaml
---
name: mojo-glibc-env-awareness
description: 'Handle Mojo projects that require newer GLIBC than the host OS provides.
  Use when: mojo fails with GLIBC version errors, pre-commit mojo-format hook fails
  due to GLIBC mismatch, or running Mojo toolchain on older Linux distributions.'
category: tooling
date: 2026-03-05
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
---
```

Mojo requires GLIBC 2.32+ but hosts like Debian 10 only provide GLIBC 2.28. Symptom:
`mojo: /lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libc.so.6: version 'GLIBC_2.32' not found`. Workaround:
`SKIP=mojo-format git commit`. CI Docker (Ubuntu 22.04+, GLIBC 2.35) enforces the check.
Only `mojo-format` requires Mojo; all other pre-commit hooks run fine on old-GLIBC hosts.

---

## Superseded from mojo-init-export-uncomment

```yaml
---
name: mojo-init-export-uncomment
description: 'Activate commented-out exports in Mojo __init__.mojo by verifying leaf-module
  implementations and using absolute import paths + comptime aliases to work around
  the v0.26.1 re-export chain limitation. Use when: (1) __init__.mojo has pending
  commented-out imports, (2) layer structs are confirmed implemented, (3) API name
  mismatches need bridging.'
category: tooling
date: 2026-03-15
version: 1.0.0
user-invocable: false
---
```

Pattern for activating commented-out imports in `__init__.mojo`: verify leaf-module
implementations with grep, use absolute leaf-module paths (not chained re-exports),
add `comptime` aliases for API name mismatches, update Public API table, and add packaging
smoke tests. Mojo v0.26.1 re-export chain limitation: `from shared.core import Linear`
fails; `from shared.core.layers.linear import Linear` works.

---

## Superseded from mojo-memory-check

```yaml
---
name: mojo-memory-check
description: Verify memory safety in Mojo code including ownership, borrowing, and
  lifetime management. Use when reviewing code or debugging memory issues.
category: optimization
date: '2026-03-19'
version: 1.0.0
mcp_fallback: none
---
```

Validate Mojo ownership and borrowing rules. Key conventions: `var` parameter takes
ownership; plain parameter = borrowed (read-only); `mut` parameter = mutable reference.
Use `^` operator only for ownership transfer. `mut self` for mutating methods; `out self`
only for `__init__`. List/Dict/String are non-copyable — must use `^` when returning.

---

## Superseded from mojo-package-level-reexports

```yaml
---
name: mojo-package-level-reexports
description: 'Add convenience top-level re-exports to a Mojo package __init__.mojo.
  Use when: enabling `from shared import X` style imports, activating commented-out
  import lines after implementation is ready, adding optimizer structs (AdaGrad/RMSprop/AdamW),
  or extending an existing re-export group with new symbols.'
category: architecture
date: 2026-03-07
version: 2.0.0
user-invocable: false
---
```

Workflow for top-level re-exports: find canonical defining module (grep `^struct`),
audit active imports vs commented blocks (commented blocks may reference stale/wrong
submodules), add absolute import from the defining module, update Public API table comment,
add import test. Verified on ProjectOdyssey PRs #3738 (SGD/Adam/AdamW) and #4785
(AdaGrad/RMSprop). Critical: commented-out blocks like `# from .training.optimizers
import SGD, Adam, AdamW` may point to the wrong module — always verify with grep first.

---

## Superseded from mojo-reexport-import-tests

```yaml
---
name: mojo-reexport-import-tests
description: "Mojo re-export: add import tests for package re-exports, wire structs
  through multi-level __init__.mojo chains with canonical aliases, and audit submodule
  __init__.mojo files for re-export limitations. Use when: (1) adding exports to
  __init__.mojo and verifying package public API, (2) a struct exists in a leaf
  module but is missing from parent package imports, (3) a follow-up issue asks
  to check if re-export limitations affect sibling submodules, (4) a docstring audit
  reveals undocumented submodules."
category: testing
date: 2026-03-07
version: 2.0.0
user-invocable: false
tags:
  - mojo
  - reexport
  - imports
  - __init__.mojo
  - package-api
  - alias
  - docstring
  - audit
---
```

Consolidated skill (v2.0.0) covering three sub-workflows: (1) adding import tests for
package re-exports (≤10 `fn test_` per file; update both `test_imports.mojo` and
`test_imports_part1.mojo`); (2) chain wiring — add re-exports to intermediate `__init__.mojo`
then import from leaf module at root (not from intermediate); (3) limitation audit — grep
for `# NOTE.*[Rr]e-export` patterns, document clean vs limited submodules. Always check
`__init__.mojo` first — the re-export is often already present; only tests are missing.

