## Superseded from mojo-sanitizer-build-scope-and-tcmalloc-incompat

```yaml
---
name: mojo-sanitizer-build-scope-and-tcmalloc-incompat
description: "Scope Mojo ASAN/TSAN builds to shared-library-only + per-test compile,
  not full binary AOT. Document the known TSAN/tcmalloc startup abort. Use when:
  (1) adding --sanitize modes to a Mojo build, (2) sanitizer sweeps OOM partway
  through, (3) TSAN binaries abort with FATAL: ThreadSanitizer: unexpected memory mapping."
category: testing
date: 2026-05-11
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-ci
tags: [mojo, sanitizer, asan, tsan, tcmalloc, build-scope, oom, justfile, mojo-1-0]
---
```

Two-phase build pattern: Phase A packages the shared library for all modes; Phase B
short-circuits for sanitizer modes (prevents OOM from 46 parallel AOT builds on ≤16 GiB
hosts). TSAN compile requires `-j1` (workaround for `modular/modular#6413`). TSAN runtime
aborts with tcmalloc/ThreadSanitizer shadow-memory incompatibility before `main()` — this
is a Modular-side issue, not user code. Verified in ProjectOdyssey PR #5389: ASAN 298/298
tests passed with 46 leaks; TSAN 298/298 binaries aborted at startup.

