## Superseded from mojo-sanitizer-support-matrix

```yaml
---
name: mojo-sanitizer-support-matrix
description: "Use when: (1) running mojo build --sanitize=thread and hitting
  DW.ref.__gcc_personality_v0 linker error, (2) trying --sanitize=memory or
  --sanitize=undefined and getting invalid sanitizer error, (3) deciding which
  sanitizer to use to escalate a non-deterministic Mojo runtime crash, (4)
  interpreting a clean ASAN run alongside a persistent libKGEN crash."
category: debugging
date: 2026-05-09
version: "1.0.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-local
tags: [mojo, sanitizer, asan, tsan, msan, ubsan, debugging, mojo-1-0, upstream-issue]
---
```

Mojo 1.0.0b2 sanitizer support: ASAN works; TSAN fails at link time (`duplicate symbol:
DW.ref.__gcc_personality_v0`, filed as `modular/modular#6512`); MSAN and UBSAN are compiler-
rejected (`invalid sanitizer 'X', expected one of: 'address' or 'thread'`). ASAN instruments
user code only — pre-built `libKGEN*`/`libAsync*`/`libMSupport*` are NOT instrumented.
Decision rule: clean ASAN + persistent `libKGEN` crash = bug in Mojo runtime itself; escalate
upstream. Verified on ProjectOdyssey PR #5364.
